<HEADLINE> Oslo to Host Conference on Child Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- An International Conference on
Child Labor will be held in Oslo, Norway, on October 27-30, the
United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the conference, to be hosted by the Norwegian
government with the participation of the International Labor
Office (ILO) and UNICEF, is to contribute to the development of
new strategies to eliminate child labor at national, regional and
international levels.
</P>
<P>
According to new estimates quoted by UNICEF, more than 250
million children between the ages of five and 14 work today around
the world, in countries rich and poor.
</P>
<P>
Many of the children are at risk from hazardous and intolerable
forms of labor. Many are denied education and trapped in cycles of
poverty. Their most basic rights, their health and even their
lives are sometimes placed in jeopardy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
