<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zamorano to Join Chile in Last World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chile's international striker
Ivan Zamorano said he would not miss the decisive World Cup
qualifier against Bolivia on November 16.
</P>
<P>
Zamorano, who plays in Inter club of Italy, has been absent
from three qualifying matches due to a pulled muscle.
</P>
<P>
A win of the decision will send Chile on the way to the 1998
France finals. The other three qualifying teams in South American
zone are Argentina, Colombia and Paraguay, alongside with
defending champion Brazil, who qualifies for finals automatically.
</P>
<P>
"It would be very difficult for me to miss such an important
match," said the 31-year-old Chile best matchmaker, who tops the
scorers list of South American series with 12 goals.
</P>
<P>
Zamorano came back for Sunday's match against Peru, in which
Chile thrashed Peru 4-0, though he just sat on the bench watching.
</P>
<P>
He plans to fly back to Milan on Wednesday and expects to be
fully recovered soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
