<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Niger to Demarcate Joint Borders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The third phase of the
international boundary demarcation exercise between Nigeria and
the Niger Republic is to commence soon, the official News Agency
of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Saidu Aliyu, Acting Administrator of the
Jigawa State as saying that the National Boundary Commission of
Nigeria has completed preparations for the work.
</P>
<P>
Aliyu said about 15 Nigerian surveyors are currently working
in border towns in the sokoto states, trying to identify
pre-colonel boundary beacons to facilitate the demarcation.
</P>
<P>
Some of the beacons dated back to between 1907 and 1910, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have resolved to properly establish their
land boundaries, which concerns about seven states in northern
Nigeria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
