<HEADLINE> Nigeria Denies Soldiers Being Captured in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria Defense authority today
denied a media report that some 400 of its soldiers enforcing
international sanctions in Sierra Leone have been captured.
</P>
<P>
Defense spokesman Colonel Godwin Ugbo dismissed the report as
" a mere propaganda" by the military junta in Freetown, while
briefing the press at the Lagos defense headquarters.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Nigeria, which comprises the majority of the
West African Peacekeeping Force (ECOMOG), has a force of about
three battalions in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
How it is possible that one third of the Nigerian troops are
being held by the Sierra Leonean junta, he said, adding that
contrary to some media reports, the ECOMOG is holding all its
positions in Freetown.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the effects of the oil and arms embargo and other
sanctions recently approved by the UN Security Council, Ugbo said
it is working.
</P>
<P>
The sanction has caused many defections, and thousands of
refugees are now heading for Guinea, Nigeria and other
neighboring countries, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
