<HEADLINE> Kenyan Leaders Promise to Foster Closer Ties with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan top leaders today
hailed the country's long-term "cordial and warm" relations with
China, saying they are ready to further the Sino-Kenyan
cooperation all-round.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Vice-President George Saitoti, Foreign Minister Kalonzo
Musyoka and Speaker of the National Assembly Ole Kaparo made the
remarks when they respectively met Chinese Deputy Foreign
Minister Tian Zengpei.
</P>
<P>
Kenya values the assistance it has received from China since
its independence in early 1960s, said Saitoti, citing the
construction of Eldoret Hospital and the Moi International Sports
Complex under China's aid.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Kenyan friendship and cooperation are extended to
more and more areas, especially in agriculture, education,
construction, health, culture and sporting, he added.
</P>
<P>
He invited Chinese companies to invest in Kenya, saying there
is access from Kenya to a wide market within the East African
Cooperation, and even the whole southern and eastern African
regional markets.
</P>
<P>
Musyoka said Kenya and China have always shared common views
and supported each other within the United Nations and on other
International forums. Kenya is now a non-permanent member in the
U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Kenya highly appreciated the fact that Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, during his first-ever visit to Africa last year, put Kenya
as his first destination, said Musyoka.
</P>
<P>
"Our 'One China' policy is absolutely clear," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan parliamentary speaker also called for more frequent
exchange of visits and cooperation between the two countries and
their parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Tian commended the sound and healthy ties between Kenya and
China for years, saying the two countries face similar problems
and challenges ahead and both could learn a lot from each other.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government hopes Sino-Kenyan relations can
be enhanced to a new level through joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to its ties with Kenya, a
country of significant influence on the African continent, and is
always willing to widen and deepen its cooperation with Kenya,
Tian said.
</P>
<P>
He praised Kenya's independent, non-alignment,
good-neighborness foreign policies which pay much attention and
have made great contributions to regional peace and stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
