<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip stocks turned higher
today as the interest rates on the bond market moved lower.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average swung up and down before
closing at 8,096.29, 24.07 points higher.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a narrow margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 510.34 million shares,
up from the 351.21 million during Monday's sluggish trading.
