<HEADLINE> China Produces Its Biggest Hand-Made Carpet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Imagine a carpet so big that
80 cars could park on it.
</P>
<P>
This is exactly the kind of carpet the Deqin Carpet Factory in
east China's Zhejiang province has come up with.
</P>
<P>
The 34-meter-long, 17.8-meter-wide carpet is valued at 178,000
yuan (about 21,000 US dollars), and it needs a 5-ton lengthened
truck to transport it.
</P>
<P>
The carpet consists of one whole piece. The previous hand-made
carpet record holder was the 420-sq.m.one in the Xinjiang Hall in
Beijing's Great Hall of the People.  
</P>
