<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HIV Infection in TB Patients Rises In India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- One out of every five
tuberculosis (TB) patients in India is infected with the HIV
(human immunodeficiency virus) that causes AIDS, the Press Trust
of India said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a study published in the Indian Journal of Medical
Research, the prevalence of HIV in TB patients has shot up six
times in the past six years, rising from 3.2 percent in 1991 to 20
percent in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The increase in HIV-positive cases was steeper in the last
three years, the study said.
</P>
<P>
The high incidence of HIV among TB patients shows that HIV
infection has already made an impact on the tuberculosis situation
in India, the study added.
</P>
<P>
The study was carried out by a team of Indian scientists and
doctors who tested TB patients in Pune, Maharashtra, for HIV
infection over the last six years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
