<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wong Kam-Po Wins First Gold for HKSAR at National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Wong Kam-Po won the first gold
for Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) at the
National Games by taking the men's 180km cycling competition on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Wong, 24, clocked four hours 10 minutes and 7.50 seconds for
the historical title, the first won by HKSAR in the National Games
after it returned to China in July.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very pround to win the first gold for Hong Kong," he said
after beating a field of 56 riders.
</P>
<P>
Timothy Fok, head of the Hong Kong delegation for the Games,
said the gold will enhance the morale for other Hong Kong
athletes.
</P>
<P>
"By witnessing the fierce competition, I was as nervous as I
was awaiting my first child in the hospital," said Fok.
</P>
<P>
"Our participation in the Games and the first gold for Hong
Kong athlete, demonstrated the acknowledgement of its Hong Kong
compatriots by the motherland," he added.
</P>
<P>
As one of Asia's ace cyclists, Wong won the Tour of the
Philippines and Tour of Chinese Taipei and finished second in the
Asian Championships last year.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's Tang Xuezhong finished second with 0.34 second behind
and Tianjin's Zhang Hao settled for the bronze with 4:10:27 as
the course was shortened to 157.88 kilometers due to rains.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR has sent in a 257-member delegation with 168 athletes to
vie for medals from 20 sports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
