<HEADLINE> Largest Sino-US Joint Chemical Venture inaugurates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Amoco Chemical Asia Pacific
Ltd., the Fu Hua Group Holding Company, and the China National
Chemical Fiber Corp. here today have decided to set up the Amoco
Zhuhai Chemical Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The largest Sino-US joint venture in the chemical industry will
produce purified terephthalic acid (PTA) in Zhuhai, in Guangdong
province.
</P>
<P>
The new facility, costing 300 to 400 million US dollars, will
use Amoco's proprietary technology to produce PTA, the preferred
raw material for making polyester film, fibers, and container
resin, according to Kathryn A. Fleming, President of Amoco
Chemical China (HK).  
