<HEADLINE> Ericsson Wins Over GSM Contracts in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ericsson has gotten
113 million US dollars worth of contracts for a GSM network in
east China's Shandong province, according to Ericsson China in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth phase of expansion of the provincial GSM
network and is scheduled to go into service by the end of April of
1998, when the total handling capacity is expected to be more than
a million lines.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's mobile network has become one of the country's
largest, and the province is now one of Ericsson's largest markets
in China. It signed its first GSM network expansion contract with
the province in 1995.
</P>
<P>
China is now Ericsson's second largest market, after the US,
worldwide. The company has 19 representative offices and nine
joint ventures in China. 
