<HEADLINE> Exercise of Blocking Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Three Gorges Dam Project's
exercise of blocking the Yangtze River began today.
</P>
<P>
Yangtze, China's longest river, will be officially blocked on
November 8.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,800 workers participated in today's exercise, dumping
tons of rock into the river from both sides.
</P>
<P>
About 194,000 cubic meters of rock was dumped into the river
during the 24-hour exercise.
</P>
<P>
This broke a previous record of 146,000 cubic meters of rocks
moved in a 24-hour period, during construction of the Itaipu
Hydro-Electric Power Station by Brazil and Paraguay. 
</P>
