<HEADLINE> Soeharto Meets with Surinamese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
and visiting Surinamese President Jules Albert Wijdenbosch here
today discussed economic cooperation between the two countries, a
senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia is considering forming a kind of cooperation with
Suriname in the fishery sector, Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono
said after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
"We have much experience in developing fish and shrimp ponds,
which Suriname is also developing at present," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
While the two heads of state had a tete-a-tete, the ministers
and senior officials of the two countries held parallel meetings
on cooperation in various fields, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
At a state banquet last night in honor of the Surinamese
president who arrived here Tuesday for a four-day visit, President
Soeharto said Indonesia wanted to share its experience with
Suriname.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesia and Suriname had worked hand-in-hand through
the Non-Aligned Movement (NAM), Group-77 and the Organization of
Islamic Conference (OIC).
</P>
<P>
Soeharto also said the monetary crisis in Indonesia and other
Southeast Asian nations would obviously slow down the pace of
development.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's rupiah has dropped 46 percent against the U.S.
dollar since the beginning of this year following the speculative
attacks on the currencies in the region in July.
</P>
<P>
Jules and his party will also visit Bali and Yogyakarta from
Thursday to Friday and then return home via Singapore, officials
here said. 
</P>
