<HEADLINE> 15 Confirmed Dead in Connection with Colombo Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A total of 15 people were
confirmed dead in connection with this morning's truck-bomb
explosion in downtown Colombo, according to the Defense Ministry
of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
A truck laden with explosives broke through the security
barrier of the Galadari Hotel in the business district of Colombo
and forced its way to the hotel's loading bay before it exploded,
the ministry said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
Three security guards were shot dead by the rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) when they tried to stop
the truck.
</P>
<P>
Eight people were killed in the explosion, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It said that out of the ten terrorist suspects four have been
killed, putting the death toll to 15.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the afternoon, an officer in command told Xinhua
that five LTTE rebels were killed by the troops.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the situation is completely under control.
</P>
