<HEADLINE> Security Forces Kill 5 Rebels After Blast in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Security forces of Sri Lanka
have killed five rebels of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) involved in this morning's powerful explosion in downtown
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
An officer in command told Xinhua at the gate of the Lake House
building, in which troops were still searching for the LTTE
rebels, that so far the security forces have killed five rebels
who had conspired the explosion in the car park of Galadari Hotel,
a seaside landmark in the business district.
</P>
<P>
He said there were about seven to eight LTTE rebels who rushed
onto the road soon after the explosion. Two were immediately shot
dead when they tried to escape.
</P>
<P>
The rest forced their way into the Lake House building, which
was hundreds meters away from the Galadari Hotel. They first took
some people in the building as hostage and then released them.
Three of the rebels were killed later around noon time by
government commandos.
</P>
<P>
Fresh fighting broke out inside the building in the afternoon.
Bullets whistled over reporters and soldiers who were about 50
meters away from the building.
</P>
<P>
The clearing operation inside the building is still in process.
</P>
<P>
The explosion at 7:10 a.m. local time has killed at least five
people and injured 105 others, including 29 foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
