<HEADLINE> China Planning National Administration Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences
and Chinese Academy of Engineering today announced that they will
develop an integrated, multi-purpose administration network for
state ministries and commissions to share information resources
among offices.
</P>
<P>
China plans to build its own large-scale network the near
future, says Zhu Gaofeng, deputy president of the Chinese Academy
of Engineering.
</P>
<P>
The network will be linked to Internet for more effective
high-level management, according to Lu Xinkui, director of the
General Office of the State Council Steering Committee for
National Information Infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The problem with existing technology, Lu explains, is that it
cannot prevent hackers from breaking into the system, so Chinese
scientists are focusing on this technology now.
</P>
<P>
The two academies and the General Office will organize an
exhibition, the "China Adminisnet", from July 15 to 18, 1998 in
Beijing, on network equipment and technology, information
management equipment and technology, network application
technology, information security technology, and multimedia
technology. 
</P>
