<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Enterprises in Northeast China City Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Industrial and commercial
enterprises in Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin
Province, are developing rapidly in terms of registered capital,
but not in quantity.
</P>
<P>
By last June, the city had had 64,176 industrial and commercial
enterprises with capital topping 36.46 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
State-owned and collectively-owned enterprises lead the way in
the city's overall development. There are 10,544 State-owned
enterprises involving 14.46 billion yuan in registered capital, up
2.1 percent over last year. There are 51,315 collectively-owned
enterprises with 13.72 billion yuan in registered capital, up 8.9
percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
Since the modern enterprise system was introduced to the city,
the number of share-holding enterprises has grown to 2,086 with
7.78 billion yuan in registered capital, up 11.7 percent from last
year.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the growth rate of the number of industrial and
commercial enterprises in the city has been static at 6.6 percent,
compared with 13 percent in 1993. The number of newly registered
enterprises offsets those that have gone out of business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
