<HEADLINE> Chinese Strongwomen Break 70-kg World Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Sun Tianni of Shandong
province claimed her 70-kg weightligting title by surpassing all
the world records in the Eighth National Games here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese strongwoman lifted 120 kgs in snatch and 152.5 kgs
in jerk for a two-lift total of 272.5 kgs for the top honors.
</P>
<P>
The previous listed world records were 105 kgs in snatch, 130
kgs in jerk and 232.5 kgs in the two-lift total, all set by the
Chinese women last year.
</P>
<P>
Tang Weifang of Jiangsu province even snatched 125 kgs for the
world's best but she failed in her three attempts upon 150 kgs in
jerk.
</P>
<P>
A total of eight finalists surpassed all the three listed world
marks in the competitions.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Chinese women lifters have broke all the 18 world
records in the light six events at the National Games. 
