Hasina today called for effective measures to make the management
of cooperatives more organized and dynamic, the official news
agency BSS reported.
</P>
<P>
"We could not get the desired results of cooperatives in our
economy and society due to mismanagement, corruption and lack of
sincerity and honesty in the past," she said while addressing a
function today to mark the awarding of the national cooperative
prize.
</P>
<P>
Cooperatives have been making important contribution to poverty
alleviation and developing socio-economic condition of the poor
people, she stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cooperatives are significant in generating employment for the
poor and in increasing their income through agriculture, small
industries, fisheries, poultry and livestock, she added.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister stressed that farmers, fishermen and weavers
 should become organizers of their respective cooperatives in its
true perspective.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government is now implementing 28 cooperative
projects in the current fiscal year for the development of the
poor, have-nots and womenfolk at a cost of 1.71 billion taka
(about 38.51 million U.S. dollars), the prime minister said,
adding that such projects are being encouraged in the private
sector as they have been playing a positive role in poverty
alleviation. 
