<HEADLINE> Insurance Premiums Up, Savings Deposits Fall in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing witnessed an increase
of insurance premiums and a declining growth rate for savings
deposits in the first eight months this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Statistical Bureau, the city's
insurance premiums hit 48.3 billion yuan (5.9 billion US
dollars) for the January-August period, up 92 percent on last
year's same period.
</P>
<P>
Life insurance premiums doubled that in the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The securities market witnessed brisk business, with the trade
volume growing by 86 percent on the 1996 period to over 500
billion yuan (60 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The growth rate for rural and urban savings deposits fell with
the total volume approaching 20 billion yuan (2.3 billion US
dollars). 
</P>
