<HEADLINE> State Councilor Peng Peiyun Meets Former IUSSP Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- State Councilor Peng Peiyun,
also minister of the State Family Planning Commission, said today
that China will continue its cooperation with overseas population
scientists.
</P>
<P>
Peng made the remark during a meeting with George Tapinos,
former secretary-general of the International Union for the
Scientific Study of Populations (IUSSP), and Carmen Miro, the
organization's honorary secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
Tapinos and Miro are attending the 23rd IUSSP General
Population Conference which will run through October 17.
</P>
<P>
Peng expressed appreciation for the international
community's support for China's population studies, and noted that
the country, home to the world's largest population, should carry
out more demographic studies.
</P>
<P>
Tapinos voiced his delight and surprise over changes in China's
demographic studies, especially the large increase in the number
of population researchers over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Miro noted China's notable progress in population studies.
</P>
<P>
China Organizing Committee Chairman Jiang Zhenghua attended the
meeting along with Vice-Chairman Tian Xueyuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
