<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Welcomes Germany's New Visa Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) welcomed today Germany's
announcement that HKSAR passport holders who were frequent
travelers to Germany may be granted multiple-entry visas valid for
up to five years.
</P>
<P>
"The favorable treatment reflects a vote of confidence in the
SAR passports and signifies the strong commitment of the German
government to Hong Kong's continued success," a SAR government
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued earlier today by the Consulate General
of Germany said, the German government has decided to grant
multiple entry visas with a validity of up to five years and a
permitted duration of stay of up to 90 days per six months to
HKSAR and British National (Overseas) (BN(O)) passport holders.
</P>
<P>
"This applies especially to frequent business travelers," said
the consulate general, and "so far, visas with a maximum validity
of up to one year have been issued."
</P>
<P>
The decision was conveyed by Head of the German Foreign
Office's Legal Department Dr. Hartmut Hillgenberg to HKSAR
Director of Immigration Mrs. Regina Ip on the occasion of his
visit to Hong Kong, according to the consulate general.
</P>
<P>
The German government's decision signals its confidence in the
SAR and its government, the consulate general pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In responding to the German statement, the SAR spokesman said
that the SAR government continues to welcome German nationals to
visit Hong Kong and to enjoy visa-free stays for up to one month.
</P>
<P>
"The length of the visa-free stay period is currently under
review for possible extension," he added.
</P>
<P>
Till now, dozens of countries over the world have agreed to
accord HKSAR passport holders visa-free access or the same
treatment as BN(O) passport holders, including the United States,
Canada, France, Britain, Japan and Australia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
