<HEADLINE> HK Electronics Fair Attracts Thousands of Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Electronics
Fair, the largest-ever electronics trade fair in Asia, has
attracted many thousands of visitors from over 110 countries and
regions since it was opened in the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,100 exhibitors from 20 countries and regions are
taking part in the four-day fair, which features an eye-opening
display of eight major categories: audio visual equipment, home
appliances, electronic gadgets, computers and multimedia,
electronic and electrical accessories, telecommunication
equipment, security systems and other related services.
</P>
<P>
The China Pavilion is stronger than ever with 111 exhibitors at
the fair. "We consider this a very important fair because it is a
good chance to meet face-to-face with our buyers and at the same
time learn from our visitors," said Qiao Benyuan, president and
chief executive officer of the China National Electronics Import
and Export Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony held on Tuesday, Chairman of
the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (HKTDC) Victor Fung said
that the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region is playing an
important role in helping global companies to explore the
electronics market in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Over the next few days this fair will be a microcosm of Hong
Kong itself. Products, services and ideas will flow freely. Buyers
and sellers will come together from across China, around the
region and from all over the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Allan Wong, chairman of the Electronics Advisory
Committee of the HKTDC, said: "We now have 1,100 exhibitors in
1,600 booths occupying 33,000 square meters, up substantially from
last year's 953 exhibitors."  
</P>
</TEXT>
