<HEADLINE> Air Macao to Start Regular Flight to Fuzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao will start a daily
flight service to Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province,
from October 26.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the air company said that Fuzhou will be
the company's 6th destination on China's inland area and the 10th
destination of the company worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Passengers to take the flight will spend one hour and 25
minutes in the air for a single flight. The plane will return to
Macao on the same day.
</P>
<P>
The new service also targets Taiwanese passengers. Previously,
the air company started quasi-direct air service across the Taiwan
Straits between Taipei, Kaohsiung and five mainland destinations
including Beijing, Shanghai and Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in November, 1995, Air Macao now has a fleet of six
Airbus jetliners, with its weekly flights reaching 105 after the
new service is started.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Xiamen Airlines will start running daily air
service between Macao and Xiamen, Macao and Fuzhou from the same
day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
