<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Pledges to Strengthen Financial System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Thai monetary authorities
stated here today that a package of future measures are to be
taken to strengthen the financial system in the financial
turmoil-worn Southeast Asian country.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government has already taken a package of actions to
deal with the recent currency turmoil sweeping the Southeast Asian
region and Thailand in particular, the Thai Ministry of Finance
and the Bank of Thailand said in a joint statement circulated
during the ongoing World Economic Forum's Six East Asia Economic
Summit.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to these immediate steps, several medium-term
actions to strengthen the financial system will be taken," the
statement said, adding that "these measures include a complete
overhaul of supervisory practices as well as legal and regulatory
reforms."
</P>
<P>
It said: "This program will be supported by extensive technical
assistance from abroad. The World Bank has already agreed with the
(Thai) government on a program for such assistance."
</P>
<P>
In the next step, the statement continued, the Ministry of
Finance and the Bank of Thailand will cooperate with concerned
authorities to improve the foundation of the Thai financial
system, particularly in the part that is still outdated, to be in
line with the international standards.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the measures to be taken soon
include improving a number of laws such as the Bankruptcy Act; the
system of accounting and public disclosure; and the efficiency and
timeliness of supervision and examination of financial
institutions.
</P>
<P>
All this will be under close consultation with experts from the
International Monetary Fund and the World Bank, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Finally, it said, the experiences of the present adversity will
be used to lay the foundation for a better future and the
opportunity to achieve fundamental reforms will create a truly
strong financial system, which will give the base for future
economic growth and prosperity in the country.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's goal is to make its financial system a very
efficient one in Asia by year 2000, the statement concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
