<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saturn Bound, Cassini Probe Takes Off Aboard Space Rocket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Cassini, the probe destined
for Saturn, took off early this morning on a seven-year journey to
explore the remote planet and its rings and moons.
</P>
<P>
As the largest, most expensive interplanetary craft ever
assembled in the United States, it took a hike into space aboard a
Titan 4-B rocket blasting off from Cape Canaveral, Florida.
</P>
<P>
Delayed for weeks amid protests against a potential radioactive
catastrophe from Cassini's plutonium power source, the launch took
place at 04:43 a.m. U.S. Eastern Standard Time, or 08:43 GMT.
</P>
<P>
But preparation for the interplanetary mission, with a record
high 32 kilograms of the extremely poisonous nuclear fuel loaded
into the craft, took 11 years and cost 3.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space
Administration (NASA) said a radioactive leak is unlikely, even if
an accident happens and showers the earth with the probe's debris.
</P>
<P>
As precautions, the plutonium is in hardened ceramic pellets
encased in heat-resistant iridium and graphite to keep it from
being pulverized and dispersed into the atmosphere in an explosion.
</P>
<P>
On its billions of kilometers flight toward Saturn, Cassini is
scheduled to loop its path around the Venus, the Earth and the
Jupiter to get the gravity boost needed for closing in onto its
destination.
</P>
<P>
Ground controllers at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory in
Pasadena, California, are to monitor the probe's track throughout
the entire space odyssey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China Scores Tremendous Progress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The third generation of the
collective leadership of the Chinese Communist Party made a series
of important decisions at the Party's 14th National Congress in
1992 and 15th National Congress in 1997. During the past five years,
China has scored tremendous achievements in reform and opening-up
and in economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
At its 14th National Congress, the Chinese Communist Party made
three important decisions. Namely, the Party would seize
opportunities to speed up development, the goal of China's
economic reform was to build up a socialist market economy, and
the Party would erect Deng Xiaoping Theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics as its guideline.
</P>
<P>
The Party's decisions have pushed China's economy onto a fast
development track. From 1992 to 1996, the Gross National Product
(GNP) of China grew by 12.1 percent annually, which was 4.2
percentage points more than the average annual growth rate of 7.9
percent during the Seventh Five-Year Plan period and which also
exceeded the 10.7 percent annual growth during the Sixth Five-Year
Plan period.
</P>
<P>
The achievements of the past five years have the following
features:
</P>
<P>
-- While maintaining a rapid economic growth, the country
has effectively curbed inflation, avoiding the usual boom-bust cycle;
</P>
<P>
-- Agriculture has grown fast in a coordinated pace with
industrial growth;
</P>
<P>
-- Headway has been made in adjusting the industrial structure,
with infrastructure and basic industry developing rapidly. The
1992-1996 period saw the fastest growth rate in railway,
highway and port construction;
</P>
<P>
-- People's living standards has risen considerably, with the
annual per capita income increasing by 7.2 percent in cities and
5.7 percent in rural areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New WPC Leadership Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The leading body of the 16th
World Petroleum Congress (WPC) was elected here this afternoon at
the ongoing 15th WPC.
</P>
<P>
After three rounds of ballots, Dirk van der Meer, president of
the 15th WPC, was re-elected president of the 16th WPC at the
permanent council meeting of the 15th WPC.
</P>
<P>
Also elected was Senior Vice-president Carlos Miguel Bechelli
from Argentine, and three vice-presidents, including Wang Tao from
the People's Republic of China, Norway's Eivald Roren and
Christian Rederon of France.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Peter Ellis Jones was elected treasurer of the 16th
WPC.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the organizing committee, of the 54
members of the current WPC, 45 attended the ballots this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Five contenders for the hosting of 17th WPC due in the year
2003, comprising Brazil, Egypt, France, Indonesia and Iran, made
statement on their application.
</P>
<P>
The 16th WPC is to be held in Calgary, Canada in the year
2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China Scores Tremendous Progress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following the Party's 14th National Congress, China has made
unprecedented strides in its reform, which is aimed at building up
a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The Third Plenum of the 14th Central Committee of the CPC
in 1993 passed a resolution on a series of issues toward building a
socialist market economy, outlining a comprehensive strategy for
China's economic reform.
</P>
<P>
An overhaul of the macro-economic management system was
unveiled in 1994. During that year, breakthroughs were made in
fiscal and tax reforms, with the establishment of a tax-sharing
fiscal system and a turnover tax system centered around a
value-added tax. The different income tax rates for Chinese-funded
enterprises were unified. Also, the State Treasury is prohibited
from borrowing from the central bank, but allowed to issue bonds
to cover fiscal deficits.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector, the power of the central bank has been
greatly enhanced, which in turn has improved and diversified
the means of financial regulation. The separation of policy-oriented
banking with a commercial system has helped the specialized banks in
their transition to commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
Progress has also been made in the economic planning and
investment systems. A guideline-style planning system was
established to better regulate the macro-economy and to serve as a
control on investment in fixed assets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China Scores Tremendous Progress (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has made encouraging achievements in science and
technology, education, culture, public health, family planning,
sports and other fields since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Out of more than 150,000 items of scientific research,
some came up to the world advanced standards such as the development of
"Yinhe" super computers, computer-integrated manufacturing systems
(CIMS), a heavy ion accelerator, a free electron laser
(FEL), superconduction, satellite-based seed breeding and cloning
technology.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological circles have contributed more
significantly to the economic growth compared to five years ago,
through carrying out some national plans for conducting
high-technology research, turning advanced technology into
productive force and spreading the use of research results into
vast rural areas.
</P>
<P>
During the 1992-96 period, 153,000 people received Master's
degrees and 3.456 million students graduated from
universities. Meanwhile, over four million students completed studies
at polytechnic schools.
</P>
<P>
The number of persons with a college background has increased from
19 per 10,000 people in 1992 to 25 at present.
</P>
<P>
A total of 24.41 million illiterates have learned how to read in
the past five years, lowering the country's illiteracy rate to 12
percent from 15.8 percent in 1992.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China has made big strides in improving
socialist democratic and legal systems and modernizing national defense.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1 marked the
significant success of the concept of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Because of thorough implementation of an independent foreign
policy of peace, China is maintaining good relations with
neighboring countries and sees remarkable improvement of its
international status along with increased influence in the
international society, which creates a favorable international
environment for China's policy of opening up and modernization.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China Scores Tremendous Progress (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1994, China unified its foreign exchange rate system and put
into practice a new system of managing hard currencies. Starting
on November 1, 1996, the Renminbi yuan became convertible under
the current account.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has improved its management on important items
of imports and exports, by allowing bidding quotas for some of
exports and greatly reducing tariffs.
</P>
<P>
In reforming the pricing system, the government lifted controls
on the prices of over 95 percent of industrial commodities and
over 90 percent of farm produce.
</P>
<P>
All these reform measures have helped establish a macro-economic
regulatory system, under which the market plays a major role in
allocating resources.
</P>
<P>
During the past five years, State-run enterprises have also
been at the forefront of reform. Most large- and medium-sized
enterprises have more autonomy in daily operations and are
responsible for their own profits and losses. Quite a number of
large firms have picked themselves up from difficult situation by
merging and reorganizing assets.
</P>
<P>
The Party's 14th National Congress has boosted China's foreign
trade and cooperation. From 1992 to 1996, China's total foreign trade
volume reached 1.168 trillion U.S. dollars, representing an average
annual growth rate of 16.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the last five years, the country utilized foreign capital
totaling 204.3 billion U.S. dollars, of which 151.5 billion are
direct investment. The country now has more than 290,000 foreign-funded
ventures, 80 percent of which were established during this period.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the state foreign exchange reserve reached
105 billion U.S. dollars from 42.6 billion in 1991.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
