<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on the
Singapore market today as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index lost 23.22 points to close at 1,855.03 points.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 125.98 million units,
valued at 313.61 million Singapore dollars (about 202.33 million
U.S. dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 281 to 56, while
278 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Transit was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 20.65 million units. It was followed by the NatSteel
Elec which had 13.28 million shares traded. Public Bank Foreign
was next with 4.64 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Jurong Ship led the gainers of the day as it rose by 50 cents
to end at 6.9 Singapore dollars. NBT, OUE and the Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) increased by 20 cents each to finish at 14.8, 5.4,
and 15.7 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local computer sound card maker Creative 50
was the biggest loser as it declined by one dollar to close at
37.6 Singapore dollars. Parkway Warrant98 lost 72 cents to end at
3.48 Singapore dollars, while Jardine Matheson Holdings fell by 60
cents to finish at 7.25 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
