<HEADLINE> U.S. Rocket Blasts off to Send Probe to Saturn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A rocket blasted off early
this morning from the U.S. east coast to send an interplanetary
space probe off on a journey to Saturn.
</P>
<P>
The Titan 4-B rocket was launched from Cape Canaveral, Florida,
at 04:43 a.m. local time, or 08:43 GMT.
</P>
<P>
Aboard the launch vehicle was a plutonium-powered probe known
as Cassini and owned by the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space
Administration (NASA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
