<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Province Machine-Building Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The machine-building sector in
east China's Zhejiang Province recorded total 1996 sales of over
20 billion yuan and is expected to become the leading sector among
local industries.
</P>
<P>
The sector also ranked one of the nation's leading industries
in 1996, with sales mounting to 20 billion yuan and pretax profits
of two billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The notable achievements resulted from a local effort to help
the sector shift from extensive to intensive production by
transforming mechanisms, improving technology and attracting
foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
The sector has invested over two billion yuan in some 100 key
projects to upgrade technology, and over 100 new types of
technology applied to production have established a solid
foundation for the sector's future development.
</P>
<P>
The sector's 50 group companies currently contribute some 33
percent of total sales.
</P>
<P>
The machine-building sector currently produces more than 100
brand name products going to a number of countries and regions,
including the United States, Great Britain, Japan and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The 150-odd foreign-funded enterprises in the sector involve
total investments of well over 800 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
