<HEADLINE> McRae Leads in San Remo Auto Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Scotland finished
first with three hours, 22 minutes and 26 seconds on Wednesday in
the last stage of San Remo rally, 12th round of the world
championship.
</P>
<P>
McRae was just one second ahead of his Subaru teammate Piero
Liatti of Italy, erasing the one second Liatti led in the first
special stage. The second special was cancelled because of a
forest fire.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Sainz of Spain finished third, 14 seconds behind
McRae. World champion Tommi Makinen of Finland, who was in
competition with Sainz for the world title, was a crucial 7
seconds behind the Spaniard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
