<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Relocation Funds Spent on Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China has spent 5.31 billion
yuan to relocate residents displaced by construction of the Three
Gorges Project on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The state has budgeted 8.575 billion yuan for the resettlement
of residents affected by the first stage of dam construction.
</P>
<P>
Through June this year, 6.915 billion yuan has been spent,
according to Qi Lin, head of the Bureau for Resettlement and
Development of the State Council's Three Gorges Project
Construction Committee.
</P>
<P>
The entire relocation of residents for the gigantic water
control dam is expected to cost 40 billion yuan, which will be
distributed to Hubei province and Chongqing municipality.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, financial management organizations have been
established at central and local organizations to monitor the
distribution of resettlement funds.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to 1997, 53,000 residents and 102 factories have been
moved from the Three Gorges reservoir area. Houses with a floor
space of 1.35 million square meters have been built to provide
shelter for those displaced by construction.
</P>
<P>
Other accomplishments during construction include: 6,800
hectares of wasteland reclaimed; 2,502 water control facilities
built; 1,525 kilometers of roads constructed; 88.9 kilometers of
power transmission lines and 206 kilometers of telecommunications
lines put up; and 6.08 million square meters of land leveled in
urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Xingshan county of Hubei province and seven other units have
been cited by the Three Gorges Committee for its use of
resettlement funds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
