<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Writethru: Powerful Blast Rocks Downtown Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A powerful truck-bomb exploded
in Downtown Colombo this morning, killing at least five people and
injuring more than 100.
</P>
<P>
The bomb went off at 7:10 local time in a car park in the
Galadari Hotel, a seaside landmark in the business district of the
Sri Lankan capital.
</P>
<P>
The blast was so powerful that people living 10 kilometers off
the scene could hear the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Troops and police immediately sealed off the area, allowing
only military vehicles and ambulances to enter.
</P>
<P>
The security forces also engaged an unknown number of the LTTE
rebels, who were believed to have conspired the incident, soon
after they cordoned off the area. Several people were reportedly
injured during the crossfire.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry said in a news release at noon that the
troops "were able to kill a number of terrorists who were involved
in this explosion."
</P>
<P>
Witnesses saw at least five people were lying dead at the
scene. The National Hospital, the biggest medical facility in
Colombo, has so far admitted more than 100 injured people. Among
the injured, the hospitals said there are about 30 foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The Galadari Hotel, the Hilton Hotel, the Bank of Ceylon and
the twin-tower of the World Trade Center, which was declared open
by President Chandrika Kumaratunga on Sunday, were seriously
damaged. Several government buildings were also damaged.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the glass walls of the buildings have all fallen
down, making a mess in the area. About 50 vehicles were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Industrial Development Minister C.V. Gunaratne
denounced the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) for its
terrorist activity in Colombo when he visited those injured in the
National Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the explosion was carried out in retaliation
of the U.S. announcement that the LTTE is a terrorist
organization.
</P>
<P>
Secretary of State of the United States Madelene Albright
announced on October 8 that the LTTE, along with 29 other
organizations in the world, was on the country's terrorist
organization list and would be barred from entering and raising
funds in the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Tourism Minister Dharmasiri Senanayake also visited the wounded
in the hospital. He said the number of casualties could have been
much higher if it were not the Full Moon holiday today, on which
people do not need to work in office.
</P>
<P>
Police have tightened up their security in the capital.
Additional road blocks were also put in place.
</P>
<P>
After the bomb went off, many people fled the scene and caused
great chaos and traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year ethnic war with the
government for a separate state of their own in the north and east
of the country.
</P>
<P>
They have carried out many suicide bombing attacks in the
capital before.
</P>
<P>
On July 24, this year, a train carrying several hundred Colombo
office workers back to their home towns in the south was blasted
by two bombs at a railway station in suburban Colombo, killing
more than 90 people and injuring 400 others.
</P>
<P>
On January 31,1996, the building of the Central Bank of Sri
Lanka, which is located one block away from the Galadari Hotel,
was hit by a truck-bomb driven by LTTE suicide bombers. The
explosion killed more than 100 people and injured 1,400 others.
</P>
<P>
In October, 1995, the country's main oil storage facilities in
Colombo was destroyed by the rebels and 29 people were killed in
that accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
