<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
closed lower after reaching its 10-year high yesterday. But the
volume was solid.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index fell 6 points to 2606 with a turnover of 73
million NZ dollars (47 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Most of the leaders eased. Recent higher flier Flecther Energy
shares ended 5 cents lower to 810 cents. Air New Zealand dipped 1c
to 286c, Carter Holt Harvey lost 3c to 357c and Lion Nathan
shedded 2c to 395c.
</P>
<P>
However, Telecom shares rose 1c to 816c, and Brierley
Investment managed to maintain stable at 137c.  
