<HEADLINE> About Half Million S. Africans Use Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half a million
South Africans are using the Internet and most Internet service
providers are growing their customer base by 10 percent a month,
according to a survey.
</P>
<P>
There is a minimum estimate of about 450,000 Internet users in
South Africa, the 1997 South African internet services industry
survey compiled with the cooperation of all the major South
African service providers said.
</P>
<P>
The survey divided the Internet market into three categories:
dial-up users accessing the Internet via modems, corporate users
gaining access through company networks, and academic users
gaining access at schools and tertiary educational institutions.
</P>
<P>
A total of 154,276 South Africans are using dial-up modems via
service providers. There is an estimated 200,000 corporate users
and potentially 500,000, but not less than 100,000, users in
educational sector, the survey showed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
