<HEADLINE> Lei Li Wins 64-kg Weightlifting Title in World Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Lei Li of the Liberation Army
bettered all three world records to take the women's 64-kg
weightlifting title at the Eighth National Games here Wednesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Lei lifted 122.5 kgs in snatch and jerked up 137.5 kgs for a
two-lift total of 260 kgs, surpassing the listed records of 107.5
kgs in snatch, 130.5 kgs in jerk and 235 kgs in the total.
</P>
<P>
Both Diao Weiwei and Hou Kangfeng lifted an identical 145 kgs
in the jerk, to ranked second and third respectively in the Games.
</P>
<P>
Lei Li also broke her own national record of 117.5 kgs in
snatch, set up four years ago in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese strongwomen enjoy their world-wide dominance in the
sport which became popular in the country in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese national records usually surpass the world records
by huge margins as the latters only recognized by the
International Weightlifting Federation in its designated
international meets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
