<HEADLINE> Shoe Manufacturer Plans to Open 2,000 Chain Stores in 3 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's biggest shoemaker, the
Double Star Group, plans to open 2,000 stores in the next three
years to sell its unique brand, according to today's "Market
Daily."
</P>
<P>
Based in the coastal city of Qingdao in east China's Shandong
Province, the company grossed more than 2 billion yuan in 1996.
Two-thirds of that revenue came from the company's 600 chain
stores. The group has expanded an average 100 stores per year
since its founding in 1991.
</P>
<P>
A national conference on operating and expanding chain stores
was conducted by the State Economic and Trade Commission and the State
Commission for Economic Restructuring.
</P>
<P>
With daily turnout registering 150,000 pairs of various kinds
of shoes, Double Star's chain-store sales have allowed it to keep
its top market share over the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
