<HEADLINE> Philippine President Visits Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
and his wife, after concluding their visit to China's Hong Kong,
arrived here today beginning a three-day state visit to Myanmar at
the invitation of Chairman of the Myanmar State Law and Order
Restoration Council Senior-General Than Shwe and his wife.
</P>
<P>
Ramos and his wife were greeted by Than Shwe and his wife as
well as other Myanmar leaders and high ranking officials at the
Yangon International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Ramos will hold talks with Than Shwe later today and the two
countries will sign some agreements including that on promotion of
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for a Philippine leader to visit Myanmar
in the past several decades and is also the first trip to the
country by a leader from an ASEAN member state after Myanmar's
joining of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in
July this year.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar is President Ramos's second leg of his five-day trip to
Hong Kong and two newest members of the ASEAN -- Myanmar and Laos.
</P>
<P>
Despite few economic links between Myanmar and the Philippines
in the past decade, senior officials of the two countries
exchanged visits in recent two years.
</P>
<P>
Adviser to the Philippine President Jose T Almonte came to
Myanmar in November last year.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Foreign Minister of Myanmar U Nyunt Swe in April 1996
and Under Secretary of Foreign Affairs of the Philippines Rodolfo
C Severino in June 1997 visited each other's country.
</P>
<P>
The most recent visit of Philippine high official was that of
secretary of Economic Development Cielito Habito in August this
year.
</P>
<P>
Of the 22 countries or regions investing in Myanmar, the
Philippines injected 6.67 million U.S. dollars in a single project
at the end of September this year, according to official
statistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
