<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Hits Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring
6.8 on the Richter scale rocked the central and northern parts of
Chile today, killing at least eight people and injuring 18,
television reports said.
</P>
<P>
The tremor, with its epicenter near Combarbala, some 350
kilometers north from Santiago, lasted almost two minutes and was
felt in six departments including the Metropolitan Region of this
capital city, the Seismological Survey of the University of Chile
said. 
