<HEADLINE> Dalian to Host International Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- An international agricultural
and fisheries fair will open on October 16 -- World Food Day -- in
Dalian, northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event will display the achievements northeast
China's Heilongjiang, Jilin and Liaoning provinces have made in
local agricultural and fisheries development.
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to attract 6,000 participants, including
400 visitors from a number of countries and regions, including
Japan, the Republic of Korea, Canada and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The three northeastern provinces, along with the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region to the north, and Guizhou and Qinghai provinces
in the west, will list more than 1,000 agricultural and fisheries
projects available to domestic and overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be sponsored by United Nations Food and
Agricultural Organization, China's Ministry of Agriculture, and
local governments in Liaoning, Jilin and Heilongjiang.
</P>
<P>
The fair will also feature a series of activities to mark
World Food Day, according to the Ministry of Agriculture. 
