<HEADLINE> Shanghai Building Large Park in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai is building a
140.3-hectare park in Pudong, an economic development zone
experiencing rapid growth fueled by foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
A 20-hectare "field and garden" scenic spot has been opened to
the public. It includes an 80,000-square-meter lawn, more than
20,000 rare trees and 20 year-round flower beds.
</P>
<P>
The park construction is part of the Shanghai municipal
government's beautification project.
</P>
<P>
The park construction will be completed by 1999. It was
designed by the LUC company from Britain, winner of an
international bidding contest.
</P>
<P>
Different from most of the Chinese parks, the Pudong facility
includes a large lawn area, forest and lakes, along with
islands in the lakes, squares and international flower gardens.
</P>
<P>
The park also will be home to a number of birds, provide venues
for outdoor performances and playing areas for children.
</P>
