<HEADLINE> China Opens Its First Plant Diseases, Insect Pests TV Forecast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's first TV program on plant
diseases and insect pests opened recently in Jingmen city of
Hubei province, central China.
</P>
<P>
Previously, farmers were notified of possible plant disease and
insect pest outbreaks by mail.
</P>
<P>
The project's developer says that TV gives the information more
vividly and farmers can be promptly notified of the plant
disease or insect pest situation in their area or in neighboring
areas.
</P>
<P>
Farmers can also learn about plant disease control and about
how to eliminate pests. The programs are easy for farmers to
understand, and they can even provide the new information soon
after it appears.  
