<HEADLINE> Grassroots Technicians Honored for Contributions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Twenty grassroots technicians
who have made great contributions to scientific and technological
advancements in state-owned enterprises were honored today in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The award-winners belong to science and technology
associations, organizations for the grassroots technicians who
provide services for the enterprises' technological advancement.
</P>
<P>
During the last 10 years, the associations have launched
various technological exchanges and scientific and technological
services provided 730,000 pieces of scientific and technological
advice annually. The associations have helped the enterprises
accumulate more than 100 billion yuan (about 12.5 billion
U.S. dollars) in the last decade.
</P>
<P>
The number of associations has increased from 3,500 in 1987 to
more than 10,000 with more than 2.1 million members.
</P>
<P>
The award was provided by the Enterprise Scientific and
Technological Advancement Fund, which was established in 1994. The
fund's goal is to win support from various institutions and
enterprises at home and abroad, and to promote technological
advancement in state-owned enterprises.  
