<HEADLINE> Coach Ma Junren Appears At National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Legendary coach Ma Junren made
his apperance as expected in the Shanghai Stadium but sent a down
note about his disciples at the National Games here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"No miracles will be created before the 2,000 Olympic Games,"
said Ma who has been training a new "Ma's Family", including many
teenager runners, after the 1994 Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
Ma, who led his "Ma's Family" to dominate the women's middle
and long distance events in the track in 1993, arrived here as the
head of the Liaoning provincial athletics team instead of a coach.
</P>
<P>
He has become the centerpiece of the reporters at the National
Games, but there is no sure report about his whereabouts after the
Games opened on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Instead of staying in the star-rated hotel designated by the
Organizing Committee of the Games, he chose by himself a small and
unknown hotel in a corner of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The mysterious coach was very cautious in his talking with
coaches of other teams.
</P>
<P>
"I was not in charge of coaching the athletes," he said. "My
responsibility is to cook meals and drive cars for them. I'm a
chef and a driver here."
</P>
<P>
No body was expected to believe in his words as he was playing
possum. After coaches of other teams left, Ma came over to help
his assistant coaches in arranging training plans for his 31
disciples.
</P>
<P>
"Tell them to speed up," Ma told his assistants, shouting to
the athletes "Cheer up, cheer up!"
</P>
<P>
He signalled his athletes to relax after two-hour training.
</P>
<P>
"The rubber track here was too hard," Ma told Xinhua before he
left the stadium with his athletes at dusk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
