<HEADLINE> Indian Police Seizes Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- In a major haul of heroin
this year, Indian police seized 10 kilograms of heroin from an
Iranian national on Monday, the local press said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here on Tuesday, a senior police
officer said the consignment was meant to be smuggled out of the
country to America and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The officer said the accused, Ali Ebadullahi Kalkhoran, was
arrested from outside his rented house in South Delhi on Monday
afternoon as he was getting out of his car.
</P>
<P>
The consignment was recovered from inside the car packed in 10
plastic packs of one kilogram each in a leather bag.
</P>
<P>
The polythene covers in which the drug was packed bore markings
of a popular coffee brand to avoid detection, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The accused has been living in India for the past two years on
a certificate granted by the office of the U.N. High Commissioner
for Refugees in India.  
</P>
</TEXT>
