<HEADLINE> More Congolese Refugees to be Repatriated from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 15 (Xinhua) -- More Congolese refugees
will be repatriated to their homeland with another ship to join
in the move in Lake Tanganika, according to local press today.
</P>
<P>
Vincent Parker, an official with the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), was quoted as saying here on
Tuesday that arrangements are being done to ensure the ship is
also used in the repatriation exercise.
</P>
<P>
The official said that a total of 3,435 Congolese refugees had
been repatriated from Tanzania by October 6.
</P>
<P>
Over 74,000 Congolese refugees as estimated to have fled their
country late last year to Tanzania following the out-break of
civil war in ex-Zaire which was renamed as the Democratic
Republic of Congo after the regime of Mobutu Sese Seko was
removed.
</P>
<P>
The repatriation exercise started on September 1 following a
tripartite agreement on voluntary repatriation signed by
Tanzania, the Congo and the UNHCR on August 21 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
