<HEADLINE> Croatian Deputy PM Hails Success in China Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Croatian Deputy Prime Minister
Ivica Kostovic said today that China's tremendous progress made
during its reform have left a "very deep impression" on him.
</P>
<P>
"What moves us most during our visit is that the Chinese people
are thinking of the whole of China, of its development and its
future. I have never witnessed such phenomenon in any other
countries, especially in big powers," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kostovic, also minister of science and technology, told
reporters at the airport upon his return from an official visit to
China that he was especially impressed by his visit to Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The city's industrial zone is the biggest in Asia and the pace
of its development is quickest in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said China is a big country and it has to solve
its problems by itself. Therefore China pays great attention to
the practical application of scientific research. He called on
Croatian scientists to learn from their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
During his China visit from October 6 to October 14, Kostovic
visited Beijing and Shanghai, had talks with Chinese officials on
cooperation in science and technology and signed an agreement with
the Chinese government on the establishment of a Sino-Croatian
commission on cooperation in science and technology. 
</P>
