<HEADLINE> 58 Bangladeshis Die as Bus Plunges Into Canal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- At least 58 people were killed
and 20 injured when an overloaded bus on Tuesday skidded into a
roadside ditch in Tangail district, 80 kilometers northwest of
Bangladesh's capital Dhaka, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses, the accident occurred when the driver
of the bus with more than 100 passengers on board lost control of
the vehicle. This is considered to be the worst road accident in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the disaster, the local people rushed to the
spot. Police and firefighters also rushed there and started
recovering the bodies and rescuing the injured. Among the dead, 39
are men, 10 women and nine children.
</P>
<P>
"The overloaded bus, which was supposed to carry 52 passengers,
slipped into the roadside canal when the driver tried to avert a
head-on collision with another vehicle from the opposite
direction," on injured passenger was quoted by the official news
agency BSS as saying.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has directed the
concerned authorities to investigate the cause of the the accident
and take effective measures to check such accidents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
