<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Hold Township Elections in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will hold its township
elections across the country in phases from December 1 to 31 under
a new framework of the local government body, official sources
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Chief Election Commissioner Abu Hena announced the poll
schedule at a conference of national, divisional and
district-level officials related with the election on Tuesday,
said the sources.
</P>
<P>
As per the schedule, the last date for submission of nomination
is November 3, nomination paper scrutiny November 4 and withdrawal
of candidature November 12.
</P>
<P>
Of the total 4,486 township councils, election to 4,330 will be
held in December. The five-year tenure of these councils would
have expired or will expire by May 29, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Election in the remaining 138 townships will be held later on,
the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
"The coming township election bears a great significance as it
is going to be held in a new perspective with a number of changes
in the relevant law," said the Chief Election Commissioner
announcing the poll dates.
</P>
<P>
In the newly introduced system, each township has been divided
into nine wards instead of three. From each ward one member will
be elected in general voting.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, three member posts will be reserved for the
female and they will be elected in direct voting by both male and
female voters.
</P>
<P>
Now each township will be a 13-person body consisting of one
chairman, nine general members and three members in the reserved
seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0249 </DOCNO>
