<HEADLINE> Che`S Mortal Remains Taken to Santa Clara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The coffin carrying mortal
remains of Argentine-Cuban Commander and guerrila Ernesto
"Che" Guevara and six of his dead fellows during a mission in
Bolivia departed today from the Revolution Square in Havana to
the northern city of Santa Clara.
</P>
<P>
The escorting is bound to Santa Clara by 19:00 local time
(00:00 GMT) where the mortal remains of the seven combatants will
be paid homage Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Cubans have honored the seven men since last October 11; over
200,000 Havana people gathered at the Jose Marti statue in the
Revolution Square.
</P>
<P>
Vice President of Cuba, Raul Castro, member of the Cuban
Communist Party`S Political Bureau presided the military ceremony
before the departure of the escorting toward Santa Clara, the
Radio National reported.
</P>
<P>
In the caravane there are generals, colonels and other senior
officials which were companions of "Che" Guevara during the
Cuban Revolution.
</P>
<P>
The escorting will make its way through the same route the
Ernesto "Che" Guevara military column advanced before reached
Havana in 1959 after the overthrow of the president Fulgencio
Batista.
</P>
<P>
The coffin carrying Che`s remains is escorted by the General
of Division Ramon Pardo Guerra.
</P>
<P>
The premier ceremony of the 30th anniversary of Che`s death
will be held Wednesday in Santa Clara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
