<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Kinds of Hanta Virus Found in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Two different species of
rodents to transmit the Hanta virus were found by two U.S. experts
at the Center for Diseases Control (CDC) in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said the American experts have investigated
the virus for two weeks during an outbreak in Chile and they made
their research in the southern provinces of Chile to gather
information on the incidence of Hanta virus over the population.
</P>
<P>
In a final report, the researchers said they found the possible
existence of two kinds of Hanta virus in two different rodent
species trapped in Chile.
</P>
<P>
The investigation said about 13-15 percent of the rodents in
the south of Chile is infected by the virus.
</P>
<P>
CDC experts are yet to determine if the virus found in the
second species corresponds to the kind "Hanta Andes", which
exists in Chile and Latin America.
</P>
<P>
Chilean health sources reported 20 cases of Hanta virus have
been detected in Chile, killing 12 people.
</P>
<P>
The national laboratory on Hanta virus detection and study will
be working in late November to speed up the adoption of suitable
measures to prevent the virus from continuing spreading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971015.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Irrigation System Improvement in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 20 million U.S. dollar loan to Turkey in support of a
Participatory Privatization of Irrigation Management and
Investment Project.
</P>
<P>
The project will help improve irrigation, leading to higher
crop yields and more timely and equitable water delivery.
</P>
<P>
The project is also aimed to strengthen irrigation-related
institutions, relieve the public sector of its traditional
responsibility for funding and subsidizing the cost of irrigation
operation and management.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 58.8 million dollars. In
addition to the World Bank's loan, Turkey's Water Users'
Organization will contribute 37.45 million dollars equivalent in
financing and the Government of Turkey will contribute some 1.34
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Turkey joined the World Bank in 1947, the Bank's commitment
total 12.84 billion dollars for 129 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
