announced that the LTTE, along with 29 other organizations in the
world, was on the country's terrorist organization list and would
be barred from entering and raising funds in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The National Hospital in Colombo said 30 to 40 people were
killed in the incident. The hospital, the biggest medical facility
in the Sri Lankan capital, has also admitted 88 injured people,
including two Americans. Ambulances are still moving in more
wounded.
</P>
<P>
Tourism Minister Dharmasiri Senanayake was also in the hospital
but made no comments.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Ceylon and the twin towers of the World Trade
Center, which was declared open by President Chandrika Kumaratunga
three days ago on Sunday, were seriously damaged by the car-bomb
which was planted in a car park in the Galadari Hotel.  
