<HEADLINE> Slovakia's GDP to Grow by 6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Slovak Economic Minister Karol
Cesnek said today that the gross domestic product in his country
will grow by 6 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Cesnek said industrial output is expected to grow by 9.9
percent while agricultural output by 10.5 percent. Foreign
exchange reserves will remain at 6 billion U.S. dollars level.
</P>
<P>
