<P>
"I feel greatly honored to get the prize. It belongs to
Xiaolangdi, which provided me the opportunity," Solymar said at a
ceremony held at the dam site.
</P>
<P>
Since coming to Xiaolangdi in 1995, Solymar's proposals have
proved helpful and he has shared his experience with his Chinese
colleagues and younger technicians without any reservation. One of
Solymar's proposals saved two million U.S. dollars in production
costs.
</P>
<P>
To date, approximately 700 overseas experts and engineers from
50 countries have worked on the Xiaolangdi water control project,
the largest of its kind on the Yellow River. The dam is expected
to be completed by the end of this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
