<HEADLINE> Explosion-1stadd: Blast Rocks Downtown Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A strong explosion rocked
Colombo this morning at around 7:10 local time, but the number of
casualties is not available yet.
</P>
<P>
Thick smoke can be seen over the sky of Colombo 1, the business
district of the Sri Lankan capital.
</P>
<P>
Police said the explosion took place near the Galadari Hotel, a
five-star landmark by the seaside.
</P>
<P>
Troops and police have sealed off the area, allowing only
military vehicles and ambulances to enter.
</P>
<P>
At least three ambulances have rushed to the scene while a
military helicopter was hovering over it.
</P>
<P>
Many people fled the scene and caused great chaos and traffic
jams.
</P>
<P>
Local sources close to the military said the blast was a
bombing carried out by the LTTE rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) has been fighting a
14-year ethnic war with the government for a separate state of
their own in the north and east of the country.
</P>
<P>
They have carried out many suicide bombing attacks in the
capital in the past.
</P>
<P>
One of their masterpieces took place on January 31, 1996, when
the building of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka, which is located
one block away from the Galadari Hotel, was hit by a truck-bomb
driven by LTTE suicide bombers. The explosion killed more than 100
people and injured 1,400 others.  
</P>
