<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Southwestern Province Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in
landlocked Guizhou Province has increased dramatically in the last
decade.
</P>
<P>
This southwestern China province has received 590 million
U.S. dollars since the first foreign-funded company registered in
1984. At present, 1,034 overseas-invested enterprises have settled
here, involving the equivalent of 2.19 billion U.S. dollars, with
1.59 billion U.S. dollars of foreign capital and the rest domestic
funds.
</P>
<P>
The investment mainly comes from 35 countries and regions
including Hong Kong, Taiwan, the United States, Germany, Canada
and Singapore. Investments from Hong Kong and Taiwan top the list,
constituting 70 percent and 14 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors have shifted their focus to the industrial
sector, which accounts for 77 percent of the total investment.
</P>
<P>
The number of solely foreign-funded enterprises has grown by a
large margin. They account for 25.6 percent of overseas-backed
companies, up 10 percent from 1992. end item
