<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland Reaps More Grain Despite Adverse Weather Conditions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Poland reaped 100,000 tons more
grain this year, up 0.4 percent over last year, despite adverse
weather conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Polish Central Bureau for Statistics reported today that
the grain output this year totalled 25 million tons. Potato output
dropped by 22.5 percent to 21.1 million tons, compared with that
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output of beet amounted to 15.2 million tons, with a 14.6
percent drop from the previous year. Fruit output was down 3
percent to 2.2 million tons and vegetables totalled 5.1 million
tons, about the same level of last year.
</P>
<P>
Poland has witnessed abnormal weather this year with a severely
cold and snowless winter and a late spring. Frequent heavy rains
in the summer gravely flooded 500,000 hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
The slight rise in grain output has resulted from the increase
of about 200,000 hectares of seeded land. The grain quality,
however, is inferior to that last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
