<HEADLINE> British Athletics Federation in Bankrupt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The British Athletics Federation
was plunged into a trouble because of bankrupt and unlikely to
survive when the national governing body announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The British Athletic Federation (BAF) said it had been forced
to call in interim managers to determine its future administration
because it had debts of 530,000 pounds (858,000 U.S. dollars) with
running costs of over 100,000 pounds a month.
</P>
<P>
The crisis has been caused by reduced income from sponsorship
and television while the BAF had been troubled by large legal
costs as against doping bans.
</P>
<P>
The BAF's Birmingham headquarters could be sold to meet the
deficit while the jobs of its 36 members, including national
coaches and development officers are also under threat.
</P>
<P>
However, British teams will be able to compete at competitions
such as next year's European Championships in Budapest supported
by other financial sources. 
</P>
