<HEADLINE> Pak President for Peaceful Solution of Afghan Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's President Farooq
Leghari today called for a peaceful solution of the long-running
Afghan conflict based on the participation of all parties
concerned.
</P>
<P>
The president made the call during a meeting here with a
high-level Bahraini military delegation headed by Major General
Abdullah Bin Salman Al-Khalifa, chief of staff of the Bahraini
Defense Forces.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said the continuing instability in Afghanistan is not
only a cause of concern to Pakistan but also to other countries in
the region.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan fully supports the efforts by the United
Nations and the Organization of the Islamic Conference to bring
peace and stability to the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed ways to enhance existing bilateral
relations between Pakistan and Bahrain during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Leghari stressed that the close brotherly relations between the
two countries should be strengthened by mutual support for each
other's policies and priorities, both in regional context and
internationally.
</P>
<P>
Al-Khalifa expressed his hope that the relationship between
Bahrain and Pakistan would be further strengthened in the future.
 
</P>
