<HEADLINE> Olympic Medalist Plaza Banned for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Daniel Plaza, who won a
gold medal in the 20-km walk at the 1992 Barcelona Olympics, has
been suspended for two years after failing a dope test last year.
</P>
<P>
The athlete tested positive for the steroid nandralone after
the 1996 Spanish championships in Malaga in June, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Plaza denied taking the drug and on Tuesday threatened legal
action against Spain's Superior Sports Council, who decided the
suspension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
