<HEADLINE> Brazil, U.S Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- United States and Brazil
signed today in Brasilia seven accords upon cooperation in
different sectors.
</P>
<P>
Brazil`S President Fernando Henrique Cardoso and U.S.
President Bill Clinton were present during the signing
ceremony at the Planalto Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
The documents signed were on education, public administration
modernization, judicial, technological, environmental and space
cooperation and the peaceful use of nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
The accord on education, described as the most important one
reached during Clinton's visit, states both countries will take
joint actions involving interchanging experiences and training of
university teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
The document on judicial system would allow Brazil`s judicial
system to count on U.S. support to punish fugitives from Brazil to
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The contract on peaceful use of nuclear energy involves the
interchange of information and technology for medical issues and
food production.
</P>
<P>
The energy accord involves cooperation on suitable, advanced
technology for production of energy, as well as replaceable
energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
