<HEADLINE> Rafter Upset in First Round of Lyon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Open champion Pat Rafter
of Australia was eliminated by French wild card Arnaud Clement in
straight sets 3-6, 6-7 (5-7) at the ATP tournament in Lyon, France
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, 24, number three in the world and top seed here, played
as a first round casualty together with Spanish third seed Alex
Corretja who lost three sets to compatriot Julian Alonso.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Clement, who ranked 109 in the world, ousted
Spaniard Sergi Bruguera in Vienna last week.
</P>
<P>
Earlier the 1996 Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek of the
Netherlands, seeded six, breezed through his first round by
beating Moroccan Hicham Arazi 6-3, 6-3. 
</P>
