<HEADLINE> China Makes New Progress in Promoting Respect, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- China had made new
progress in promoting the respect and acceptance, the
dissemination and wider appreciation of the principles of
international law, Qin Huasun, Chinese permanent representative to
the United Nations, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Sixth Committee (Legal), Ambassador Qin said the
reform and the opening-up over the last two decades had vigorously
promoted the development of China in the political, economic,
social and cultural fields, and broadened on a large scale the
scope of interaction and cooperation between China and the rest of
the world.
</P>
<P>
Qin said that against this backdrop, the legal framework in
China was being gradually completed, and rule of law over all
respects of social life was rapidly gaining weight. Legal
awareness and knowledge, including that of international law, had
been widely spread among the people. This was highly significant
for China in its commitment to the policy of reform and
opening-up, and in its renewed efforts to participate in
international exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said that the Chinese government and its people
had made new progress in promoting the respect and acceptance of
the principles of international law. China, amidst reform and
opening-up, enjoyed social stability and economic growth, thus
providing more adequate guarantee for improving human rights of
the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Qin said China would sign the international Covenant on
Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, and was carefully studying
the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights. The
principle of universality of human rights would receive
increasingly wider respect in China.
</P>
<P>
Qin said China had long adopted a positive attitude towards the
actions of the UN Decade of International Law. The Chinese had
hosted several seminars under the Program of Actions dedicated to
the Decade, and participated in a number of other actions under
the Programs. During the final term of the Decade, China would
work closely with others to make active contribution to the
successful conclusion of the Decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
