<HEADLINE> Egypt's Flag Carrier Opens New Air Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Egypt Air, the national flag
carrier, for the first time opened an international air link today
to Assuit, infamous for Islamic extremist activities in southern
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The new route linking Cairo to Kuwait via Assuit, about 320
kilometers south of the Egyptian capital operates every Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It is part of the government's drive to refurbish Assuit's
image as a favorite hideout of the Muslim militants that have been
fighting against the secular government since 1992.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,225 people have been killed in the fight between
the Muslim militants and police over the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
